# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1993-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The **1993 FIVB World Grand Prix** was the first edition of the women's volleyball tournament, annually arranged by FIVB.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1993-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] It was played by eight countries from 28 May to 30 June 1993.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1993-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The final round was staged in Hong Kong.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1993-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The top six teams in the preliminary round advance to the final round.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1994-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The **1994 FIVB World Grand Prix** was the second edition of the women's volleyball tournament, annually arranged by FIVB.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1994-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] It was played by eight countries from 19 August to 11 September 1994.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1994-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The host China and top three teams in the preliminary round advance to the final round.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1995-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The **1995 FIVB World Grand Prix** was the third women's volleyball tournament of its kind, played by eight countries from 18 August to 17 September 1995.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1996-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The **1996 FIVB World Grand Prix** was the fourth women's volleyball tournament of its kind.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1996-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] It was held over four weeks in eight cities throughout Asia, cumulating with the final round in Shanghai, PR China, from 27 to 29 September 1996.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1997-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The **1997 FIVB World Grand Prix** was the fifth women's volleyball tournament of its kind.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1997-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] It was held over four weeks in eight cities throughout Asia, cumulating with the final round in Kobe, Japan, from 29 to 31 August 1997.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1997-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The best three teams from the overall ranking and Japan as host are qualified for the final round.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1998-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The **1998 FIVB World Grand Prix** was the sixth women's volleyball tournament of its kind, played by eight countries from 21 August to 13 September 1998.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1998-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The best four teams from the overall ranking are qualified for the final round.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1999-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The **1999 FIVB World Grand Prix** was the seventh women's volleyball tournament of its kind.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/1999-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] It was held over three weeks in four cities throughout Asia, cumulating with the final round in Yu Xi, PR China, from 27 to 29 August 1999.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The **FIVB World Grand Prix 2007** was the fifteenth edition of the annual women's volleyball tournament, which is the female equivalent of the Men's Volleyball World League.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The 2007 World Grand Prix lasted four weeks with a total number of 65 matches.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] During the first, second, and third week, each team played nine matches in total.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] Preliminary rounds were staged in Japan (3x), Italy, Poland, Macau, Hong Kong, Russia, and Chinese Taipei.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The final round was played in Ningbo, PR China, at Beilun Gymnasium, over five days and the best six teams from the preliminary rounds.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] A round robin system was played to decide the 2007 World Grand Prix Champion.
[src:2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix/2007-fivb-volleyball-world-grand-prix] The host China and top five teams in the preliminary round advance to the final round.
